.TH "remap_pfn_range" 9 "remap_pfn_range" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
remap_pfn_range \- remap kernel memory to userspace
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" remap_pfn_range
.BI "(struct vm_area_struct *vma "  ","
.BI "unsigned long addr "  ","
.BI "unsigned long pfn "  ","
.BI "unsigned long size "  ","
.BI "pgprot_t prot "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vma" 12
user vma to map to
.IP "addr" 12
target page aligned user address to start at
.IP "pfn" 12
page frame number of kernel physical memory address
.IP "size" 12
size of mapping area
.IP "prot" 12
page protection flags for this mapping
.SH "NOTE"
this is only safe if the mm semaphore is held when called.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, negative error code otherwise.
